  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Life-Saving Assistance and Health Care Services to Migrants and Refugees from Venezuela in Brazil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In March 2020, in view of the COVID-19 global pandemic, Brazil has declared a national emergency, ordered the closure of its national borders and imposed several restrictions on economic activities and population mobility. The rapid spread of the disease and its immediate socioeconomic consequences have created new challenges to all vulnerable populations in Brazil and severely impacted the situation of Venezuelan migrants and refugees living in the country. The overall objective of this project is to improve life-saving emergency assistance to Venezuelan migrants and refugees in the state of Roraima. In the context of the pandemic and in line with the regional Refugees and Migrants Response Plan (RMRP) 2021, the proposed intervention focuses on providing food and non-food item assistance and improving health care services to migrants and refugees.</narrative>
  </description>
